element.name: Stargate P53006 TB Cache by Fjon, Traditional Cache (1/1)

h4.font: Put simply, any travel bug arriving at a Stargate TB Cache can be rapidly transported to another Stargate TB Cache for eventual pickup.

element.long-description:
Any travel bug arriving at a Stargate TB Cache can be rapidly transported to another Stargate TB Cache. If a TB is left at this cache with a valid Stargate address, the TB will be transported to that specified Stargate TB Cache (for example: if "P3898" is included in the log entry or on a physical note attached to the TB, that TB will arrive at the Stargate P3898 TB Cache, Central Kansas, USA). If the TB is left without a valid Stargate address, or has an invalid address, it will be transported to a cache that best advances its goal (in the cache owner's opinion), or denied access to the Stargate Network if no Stargate TB Cache advances its goals.
If a TB owner doesn’t want their TB to travel the Stargate network, quickly contact me (Fjon) and I’ll revoke its traveling orders. If the cacher dropping off the TB doesn’t want the TB to travel the Stargate network, include this information in the cache log (both paper and web). The TB will be assigned local support duty.
Anyone interested in establishing a Stargate TB Cache that’s at least 500 miles from any other Stargate TB Cache please contact drossdross -P4079
At present, the following Stargate TB Cache sites are known to exist in the geoworld: Stargate P4079 TB Cache (Western PA)

TBs traveling outside Europe may require multiple wormhole trips to intermediate Stargates to complete their mission. Additionally, a Zero Point Module (ZPM) may be required. Logistics to arrange multiple trips and/or to secure a ZPM may take several weeks or more. If the TB’s Commanding Officer (i.e., owner) does not want the TB to volunteer for such a lengthy, long-distance mission, just quickly contact the owner of originating Stargate TB Cache (me, Fjon, for P53006) and they will revoke the TB’s travel orders - and reassign the TB to local support duties (i.e., redirect the TB to local caches).
The Cache:
This cache is located in my local park. Parking can be found at N53 15.641 W006 09.757. From there follow the path on the left - the one on the right is a dead end. Please be careful when climbing over the rocks at the cache location.
The park is open from 10:00 to 20:00 during the summer, and 10:00 to 17:00 during the winter.
You may sign the log and trade items just like an ordinary cache though!
